WEBVTT

00:00.420 --> 00:03.620
♪♪

00:04.080 --> 00:07.080
Previously on Shadowhunters...
Warlocks, werewolves, vampires,

00:07.080 --> 00:09.170
Seelies, they're making them
all mundane by injecting them

00:09.170 --> 00:10.460
with heavenly fire.
It didn't work.

00:10.460 --> 00:12.080
ALEC: The formula
must be too weak.

00:12.080 --> 00:14.170
IZZY: Each vial of serum
contains nanoparticles

00:14.170 --> 00:15.500
of Glorious. I can
use them to create

00:15.500 --> 00:17.120
a new, more potent formula.

00:17.120 --> 00:19.250
As long as you're here...
I'll be fine.

00:20.250 --> 00:21.290
(GRUNTING)

00:23.000 --> 00:23.670
CLARY!

00:23.960 --> 00:25.040
Jace...

00:25.040 --> 00:26.540
Hello, sister. Join me.

00:26.540 --> 00:28.250
We're coming.

00:28.250 --> 00:30.170
(GROANING) Clary?

00:30.170 --> 00:31.250
I love you, Jace,

00:31.250 --> 00:32.460
but I won't let you stop me.

00:32.460 --> 00:34.250
SEELIE QUEEN: While the
Shadowhunters are away,

00:34.250 --> 00:37.120
get to Jonathan
and pierce his heart.

00:38.210 --> 00:39.380
I won't let anyone hurt you...

00:39.380 --> 00:40.420
big brother.

00:40.420 --> 00:42.460
You came for me.

00:42.460 --> 00:43.500
Raphael?

00:43.500 --> 00:45.330
Are you a Daylighter now?
No...

00:45.330 --> 00:47.040
I'm human.

00:47.040 --> 00:48.290
Jordan... I want you to stay.

00:49.500 --> 00:52.380
For the pack.
And how is my son?

00:52.380 --> 00:55.210
I'm here to get him his magic
and his immortality back.

00:55.210 --> 00:58.170
Break his heart.
I need a break from us.

00:59.540 --> 01:02.380
Oh, no, no, no.
I can't lose you too, Alec.

01:02.380 --> 01:03.500
I'm sorry.

01:03.500 --> 01:05.330
(RISING MUSIC)

01:08.330 --> 01:10.540
(GUSTING WIND)

01:21.460 --> 01:23.210
My boy...

01:28.290 --> 01:31.250
How'd you get here?
What fool summoned you?

01:31.250 --> 01:33.540
A father's love knows no bounds.

01:33.540 --> 01:37.170
I could feel your pain all the
way from Edom. I had to come.

01:37.170 --> 01:38.250
Stay away from me!

01:38.250 --> 01:40.170
You misunderstand, Son.

01:40.170 --> 01:42.170
Oh, no, no, no, no.
I completely understand.

01:42.170 --> 01:44.540
You're here to spread your
darkness, it's what you do.

01:44.540 --> 01:47.580
No. Today, I come to give you

01:47.580 --> 01:49.380
back what's rightfully yours.

01:49.380 --> 01:52.420
(CRACKLING ENERGY)

01:52.420 --> 01:54.250
(GRUNTING)

01:54.250 --> 01:56.380
(HEAVY BREATHING)

01:58.500 --> 02:00.500
(ENERGY CRACKLING)

02:05.120 --> 02:06.540
My magic...

02:06.540 --> 02:09.120
(SOFT MUSIC)

02:18.170 --> 02:19.500
What do you want?

02:19.500 --> 02:21.330
What every father wants...

02:21.330 --> 02:22.620
to see their child happy.

02:22.620 --> 02:25.210
With you there's always a price.

02:25.210 --> 02:28.420
Not this time. In the centuries
since you've banished me,

02:28.420 --> 02:30.330
not a day has passed
when I haven't felt

02:30.330 --> 02:31.620
the pain of losing you.

02:33.620 --> 02:35.580
I took your magic...

02:36.580 --> 02:38.500
...to bring you closer.

02:40.420 --> 02:42.290
That was wrong.

02:42.290 --> 02:44.580
All I want is another chance

02:44.580 --> 02:46.580
to be your father again.

02:56.250 --> 02:57.290
Too late.

02:59.330 --> 03:01.540
I won't take no for an answer.

03:01.540 --> 03:04.170
You don't really have a choice.

03:04.170 --> 03:06.250
(GUSTING WIND)

03:06.250 --> 03:08.620
(TENSE MUSIC)

03:10.330 --> 03:13.710
♪ We're coming

03:13.710 --> 03:17.250
♪ After you

03:17.250 --> 03:21.290
♪ This is the hunt

03:21.290 --> 03:24.380
♪♪♪

03:29.250 --> 03:31.380
♪ This is the hunt ♪

03:36.460 --> 03:38.420
I don't understand. You said
if you stayed with her,

03:38.420 --> 03:40.290
nothing bad could happen.
I only lost sight of her

03:40.290 --> 03:41.460
for a minute.
Enough time

03:41.460 --> 03:42.620
for the Twinning rune
to have taken hold.

03:42.620 --> 03:44.580
And once I got back to her,
it was already too late.

03:44.580 --> 03:46.250
She'd been completely overtaken.
Jace!

03:46.250 --> 03:47.380
Alec, where were you?!

03:47.380 --> 03:48.670
I got the alert. You OK?

03:48.670 --> 03:50.710
I will be
when we get Clary back.

03:52.420 --> 03:53.620
What about you? Everything OK?

03:53.620 --> 03:55.250
I'm fine.

03:55.750 --> 03:57.460
Number one priority is Clary.

03:57.460 --> 03:58.710
The Clave has reinstated
the kill order

03:58.710 --> 04:00.580
on her and Jonathan.
What?! You can't let them

04:00.580 --> 04:02.580
do that. You have to fight it.
You're the head of an Institute.

04:02.580 --> 04:04.420
No, no, no.
This is a Clave order.

04:04.420 --> 04:06.330
We just have to get
to Clary before they do.

04:06.330 --> 04:07.580
What's the latest on
the Heavenly Fire serum?

04:07.580 --> 04:09.620
I'm still extracting
particles of Glorious.

04:09.620 --> 04:11.460
Once I'm done, I should
be able to create

04:11.460 --> 04:12.620
a more concentrated serum

04:12.620 --> 04:14.620
that's much more powerful
than the one we tried before.

04:14.620 --> 04:16.540
And if you inject
Jonathan with that?

04:16.540 --> 04:18.750
That should separate
Clary from Jonathan for good.

04:18.750 --> 04:21.290
OK. That's great and everything,
but first we have to find them.

04:21.290 --> 04:22.500
Jonathan and Clary
will have activated

04:22.500 --> 04:24.580
their Anti-Tracking runes.
Finding them won't be easy.

04:27.420 --> 04:29.380
It will if they come to me.

04:35.750 --> 04:38.540
Champagne. Fancy.

04:38.540 --> 04:40.330
Well, it is a special occasion.

04:41.580 --> 04:42.790
You saved me, Clary.

04:42.790 --> 04:45.500
You would do the same for me.

04:45.500 --> 04:47.290
I would die for you.

04:48.500 --> 04:50.380
I've spent so long
dreaming of the day

04:50.380 --> 04:51.460
that we'd finally be together.

04:53.710 --> 04:54.710
To us.

04:55.710 --> 04:56.750
To us.

04:58.620 --> 05:01.710
(AMBIENT MUSIC)

05:04.460 --> 05:05.710
Something's troubling you.

05:07.380 --> 05:08.620
Isabelle and the others

05:08.620 --> 05:10.710
are working on a stronger serum

05:10.710 --> 05:12.420
to break us apart.

05:14.670 --> 05:15.790
Of course they are.

05:15.790 --> 05:17.500
That doesn't concern you?

05:17.500 --> 05:19.670
No one can hurt us if we get
the Morning Star first.

05:19.670 --> 05:21.750
And once we have that sword,
the entire world

05:21.750 --> 05:23.620
will be terrified of us.

05:23.620 --> 05:25.620
And they will finally
leave us in peace.

05:25.620 --> 05:28.580
But the Seelie Queen said
she will only give you

05:28.580 --> 05:30.830
the Morning Star sword if you
bring her Lilith's head.

05:30.830 --> 05:32.790
Well, those were her terms.

05:32.790 --> 05:34.420
(CHUCKLING)

05:34.420 --> 05:36.330
You up for a trip to Prague...

05:36.330 --> 05:37.500
little sister?

05:39.500 --> 05:40.710
Can't wait.

05:40.710 --> 05:43.710
(GUSTING AIR)

05:44.790 --> 05:46.710
From your Shadowhunter friends?

05:46.710 --> 05:48.420
It's from Jace.

05:48.420 --> 05:50.620
He wants to meet.
He says his love for me

05:50.620 --> 05:53.460
matters more than his loyalty
to the New York Institute.

05:53.460 --> 05:56.790
And to prove it, he'll help us
get back our family sword.

05:56.790 --> 05:58.460
No. It's a trap.

05:58.460 --> 06:00.500
He just wants to come between us
like he did before.

06:00.500 --> 06:01.670
He no longer has that power.

06:02.670 --> 06:04.750
I'm with you because
I want to be with you.

06:06.710 --> 06:08.670
Well, then why do you
even need him?

06:08.670 --> 06:11.620
Jonathan... you're my brother,

06:11.620 --> 06:13.670
and I never want us to be apart.

06:13.670 --> 06:16.540
But... I'm in love with Jace.

06:17.540 --> 06:18.710
I can't live
without him, either.

06:18.710 --> 06:20.830
He wants me dead, Clary.

06:22.750 --> 06:25.710
Not if I tell him that I
can't live without you.

06:25.710 --> 06:28.460
To be with me,
Jace would accept that.

06:28.460 --> 06:30.580
He loves me more than
anything in this world.

06:30.580 --> 06:33.620
I love you more than
anything in this world!

06:36.420 --> 06:37.620
Isn't that enough?

06:40.420 --> 06:41.830
I want to hear Jace out.

06:43.620 --> 06:45.500
If you love me...

06:47.460 --> 06:48.500
...come with me.

06:48.500 --> 06:50.750
(RISING MUSIC)

06:54.500 --> 06:55.670
(SIGHING)

06:55.670 --> 06:57.710
Patience is just not my thing.

06:57.710 --> 06:58.880
Yeah. Me neither.

07:04.830 --> 07:06.920
So, about last night...

07:06.920 --> 07:08.580
when you and I were both...
...alone?

07:11.750 --> 07:13.500
(BEEPING)

07:13.500 --> 07:14.580
Perfect timing.

07:22.710 --> 07:24.670
Pure Heavenly Fire...

07:24.670 --> 07:25.710
Wow...

07:26.880 --> 07:28.500
What's happening?

07:31.880 --> 07:33.540
(CRACKING)

07:35.620 --> 07:36.750
Whoa...

07:36.750 --> 07:38.580
Simon, don't!
What?

07:38.580 --> 07:40.670
Aldertree diluted
Glorious's power

07:40.670 --> 07:43.540
because its concentrated form
was lethal to Downworlders.

07:45.710 --> 07:47.540
Not to be a buzz kill,

07:47.540 --> 07:50.790
but... how do we inject
Jonathan with a rock?

07:50.790 --> 07:51.580
No clue.

07:55.580 --> 07:56.920
What about the Iron Sisters?

07:56.920 --> 07:58.710
They're badass weapon-makers.

07:58.710 --> 08:00.880
Can't they help?
Glorious was an Angelic relic.

08:00.880 --> 08:03.710
You know what they'd do if they
knew we even had a piece of it?

08:04.830 --> 08:06.830
Probably not grind it through
a centrifuge to save Clary.

08:09.880 --> 08:12.790
You know something?
There is one Iron Sister

08:12.790 --> 08:13.920
that doesn't play by the rules.

08:13.920 --> 08:15.920
Luke's sister.
Yeah.

08:18.960 --> 08:21.830
(SENTIMENTAL MUSIC)

08:31.750 --> 08:33.750
♪ Thought I'd found a way

08:35.670 --> 08:37.670
♪ I thought I found a way

08:38.670 --> 08:39.880
Where are we going?

08:39.880 --> 08:41.620
I told you, it's a surprise.

08:41.620 --> 08:43.040
I don't like surprises.

08:43.040 --> 08:44.670
What do you mean?

08:44.670 --> 08:45.960
You're the king of them.

08:45.960 --> 08:47.790
You know, you start waving
your hands around,

08:47.790 --> 08:49.580
I never know what's gonna
show up in front of me.

08:50.750 --> 08:52.620
OK. So...

08:52.620 --> 08:55.670
There's something...
I wanted to do.

08:55.670 --> 08:56.880
Oh, you want to lock me up?

08:57.960 --> 08:58.960
I thought you'd never ask.

08:58.960 --> 09:00.620
No... no.

09:00.620 --> 09:03.000
Remember that bridge
you brought me to

09:03.000 --> 09:04.580
in Paris last week,

09:04.580 --> 09:06.540
the one where people
put those locks?

09:07.580 --> 09:08.790
To show their eternal love.

09:08.790 --> 09:11.710
Right. Well, they have
a place like that here

09:11.710 --> 09:12.790
in New York too.

09:15.960 --> 09:18.040
Look, I don't know.
I... I know it's silly.

09:18.040 --> 09:19.880
I wanted us to have a lock too.

09:21.710 --> 09:23.830
♪ Walking out of time

09:26.000 --> 09:28.670
♪ Looking for a better place

09:30.790 --> 09:31.880
What does that say?

09:31.880 --> 09:33.750
Aku cinta kamu.

09:34.750 --> 09:36.710
♪ Always in my headspace

09:36.710 --> 09:38.000
Indonesian for I love you.

09:38.000 --> 09:42.960
♪ Someday, I'll make it

09:42.960 --> 09:45.750
♪ Out of here

09:45.750 --> 09:48.000
♪ Even if it takes

09:48.000 --> 09:53.920
♪ All night or 100 years

09:53.920 --> 09:56.670
♪ I need a place to hide

09:56.670 --> 09:59.620
♪ But I can't

09:59.620 --> 10:02.000
♪ Find one near

10:02.000 --> 10:03.080
♪ I wanna feel

10:03.080 --> 10:06.830
♪ The life outside

10:06.830 --> 10:11.000
♪ I can't find my fear

10:12.000 --> 10:14.080
♪ Isn't it lovely?

10:14.080 --> 10:15.790
♪ All alone

10:15.790 --> 10:17.880
♪ Heart made of glass

10:17.880 --> 10:19.960
♪ My mind of stone

10:19.960 --> 10:22.830
♪ Tear me to pieces

10:22.830 --> 10:24.620
♪ Skin to bone ♪

10:25.920 --> 10:26.960
(CRACKLING ENERGY)

10:34.880 --> 10:37.120
(SOFT MUSIC)

10:37.120 --> 10:39.670
(DOOR OPENING)

10:42.670 --> 10:44.210
Painting at the crack of dawn?

10:44.210 --> 10:46.420
Nothing says
'come join our pack'

10:46.420 --> 10:49.290
like a blood-stained wall.
It wouldn't wash off.

10:50.290 --> 10:51.540
Grab a brush.

10:54.250 --> 10:57.580
You sure you don't want
a colour with more, uh... pop?

10:57.580 --> 10:59.290
Don't even.

10:59.290 --> 11:01.580
Who saved your butt when you
had your truck painted?

11:01.580 --> 11:03.420
Saved?
Mm-hmm?

11:03.420 --> 11:06.250
OK. That blue you picked is
the color they use in nurseries

11:06.250 --> 11:07.500
to make babies fall asleep.

11:07.500 --> 11:09.170
Well, it was
a thousand times better

11:09.170 --> 11:10.580
than that Santa Claus
red you wanted.

11:10.580 --> 11:12.330
That red was classic.

11:12.330 --> 11:14.500
OK? You just didn't want me
riding around in a chick magnet.

11:16.080 --> 11:18.210
The only "chicks"
you'd have picked up

11:18.210 --> 11:21.080
are Mrs. Claus and a couple
of desperate elves.

11:22.500 --> 11:24.420
Don't give me that look.
You know I'm right.

11:24.420 --> 11:26.290
No, you... you just...

11:26.290 --> 11:27.540
you've got paint on your face.

11:27.540 --> 11:29.250
Huh.

11:30.290 --> 11:31.460
Did I get it?
Mm-mm.

11:32.540 --> 11:34.210
You want some help?

11:35.210 --> 11:36.210
Yeah? OK.

11:37.210 --> 11:38.330
Ah...

11:45.500 --> 11:47.380
♪ If you leave

11:47.380 --> 11:49.420
♪ To forget

11:49.420 --> 11:51.380
♪ If you love

11:51.380 --> 11:53.460
I can't... I can't.

11:53.460 --> 11:56.620
♪ If you leave to forget

11:56.620 --> 11:58.380
Ahem. Ahem.

11:58.380 --> 12:00.210
I'm so sorry. I...

12:00.210 --> 12:01.420
I thought it was both of us.

12:01.420 --> 12:03.330
No, it was. It's just...

12:04.500 --> 12:06.380
I wish we could go back.

12:07.460 --> 12:08.580
We can't.

12:09.580 --> 12:11.420
(DOOR OPENING)

12:15.500 --> 12:16.620
What are you doing here?

12:16.620 --> 12:18.290
What, you know this guy?

12:19.380 --> 12:20.540
We haven't met.

12:20.540 --> 12:22.420
I'm Raphael Santiago.

12:22.420 --> 12:23.620
Former head of
the New York clan.

12:25.670 --> 12:27.580
You're the one that raised
Heidi from the dead.

12:29.210 --> 12:31.380
It's a regret I'll live
with until the day I die.

12:31.380 --> 12:34.250
I'm so sorry for what
she did to your pack.

12:34.250 --> 12:35.500
I'm here to pay my respects.

12:35.500 --> 12:37.420
If you'll have them.

12:43.250 --> 12:45.420
That's OK. Um, I understand.
I'll just--

12:45.420 --> 12:46.540
How are you doing that?

12:47.540 --> 12:50.210
What?
You're standing in the sun.

12:56.460 --> 12:57.580
Simon didn't tell you?

12:57.580 --> 12:59.620
(SOFT MUSIC)

13:02.500 --> 13:04.460
Going in unarmed?
I don't like it.

13:04.460 --> 13:05.670
It's the only way to save Clary.

13:05.670 --> 13:07.620
If Jonathan smells a rat,
you're a dead man.

13:07.620 --> 13:09.250
I know. Listen, he won't.

13:09.250 --> 13:11.710
OK? We're gonna have real-time
intel on their exact location.

13:11.710 --> 13:14.290
The second Isabelle is
done with Glorious,

13:14.290 --> 13:16.500
we catch them off guard,
separate Jonathan and Clary,

13:16.500 --> 13:18.250
and then we kill him
once and for all.

13:22.580 --> 13:25.460
Now, remember, in order
for these rings to work

13:25.460 --> 13:27.620
and remain invisible, it is
imperative that you stay alert.

13:29.460 --> 13:30.540
What, do you think
I'm going to fall asleep?

13:32.250 --> 13:33.670
(CRACKLING)

13:33.670 --> 13:35.330
[Stranger things have happened.]

13:35.330 --> 13:37.670
Yeah. Hey, um...

13:37.670 --> 13:40.620
Look, I know you said the timing
wasn't right with Magnus

13:40.620 --> 13:43.290
the other day, but...

13:43.290 --> 13:44.420
why didn't you propose?

13:45.670 --> 13:47.250
(SIGHING)

13:48.500 --> 13:49.710
It's complicated.

13:52.250 --> 13:53.330
Is that why he's not here?

13:54.580 --> 13:55.750
Look, Alec...

13:55.750 --> 13:58.330
I can feel that there's
something's wrong.

14:01.580 --> 14:03.460
Magnus and I broke up.

14:05.540 --> 14:07.460
What? Why?

14:07.460 --> 14:09.250
OK. You're gonna be late.

14:09.250 --> 14:10.580
Alec, there's something
you're not telling me.

14:10.580 --> 14:12.420
What's going on?

14:14.750 --> 14:18.330
Sometimes, life just doesn't
go the way you want it to.

14:18.330 --> 14:21.580
Alec--
Please, just... go.

14:24.460 --> 14:25.580
Yeah. OK.

14:29.380 --> 14:30.500
(SIGHING)

14:33.540 --> 14:34.620
(SIGHING)

14:38.330 --> 14:39.460
I got here as soon as I could.

14:39.460 --> 14:40.670
Where's Cleophas?

14:40.670 --> 14:42.330
Not gonna make it.

14:42.330 --> 14:44.380
After she helped
Clary summon Ithuriel...

14:44.380 --> 14:45.670
when he died, I guess
part of her died too.

14:45.670 --> 14:47.670
So, now it's just us and a rock?

14:47.670 --> 14:48.670
And these...

14:52.620 --> 14:54.290
Cleophas's tools...

14:54.290 --> 14:55.380
With them, she said you could

14:55.380 --> 14:56.830
forge a new sword with
the same power as Glorious.

14:56.830 --> 14:58.790
Lilith said that stabbing
Jonathan with Glorious would

14:58.790 --> 15:00.620
sever the ties
between him and Clary.

15:00.620 --> 15:03.460
To re-forge Glorious, she said
you need to mix the alloys that

15:03.460 --> 15:05.420
you extracted with
molten Adamas

15:05.420 --> 15:06.460
and an angelic binding agent.

15:06.460 --> 15:07.750
What's the angelic
binding agent?

15:07.750 --> 15:09.420
We're gonna need Jace for that.

15:09.420 --> 15:11.460
It's angel blood,
and he's got Ithuriel's.

15:11.460 --> 15:13.670
Jace just left on mission
to find Clary and Jonathan.

15:14.170 --> 15:16.500
I guess we're gonna have
to call in our pinch-hitter.

15:19.380 --> 15:21.750
That's right! You drank Jace's
blood and became a Daylighter,

15:21.750 --> 15:24.580
which means you still have
traces of Ithuriel's blood

15:24.580 --> 15:25.620
in your system.

15:27.330 --> 15:28.460
Will this involve a needle?

15:29.670 --> 15:32.330
(SONOROUS VIBRATION)

15:34.790 --> 15:36.790
(TENSE MUSIC)

15:42.540 --> 15:44.460
My sister made me
promise not to kill you

15:44.460 --> 15:45.830
unless this is an ambush.

15:45.830 --> 15:47.710
Maybe it's my lucky day.

15:51.420 --> 15:52.580
I'm happy to see you.

15:52.580 --> 15:54.790
But I was trained by the best,

15:54.790 --> 15:56.540
so first things first.

16:00.460 --> 16:02.380
I came with no weapons,
no stele.

16:02.750 --> 16:03.790
He's clean.

16:03.790 --> 16:05.790
As much as I want you with me,

16:05.790 --> 16:07.540
you killed my brother once.

16:07.540 --> 16:09.460
And if it wasn't
for our connection,

16:09.460 --> 16:10.620
I suspect you'd do it again.

16:10.620 --> 16:12.670
I look forward to the re-match.

16:12.670 --> 16:14.380
There will be no re-match.

16:15.790 --> 16:17.580
I want both of you alive.

16:20.670 --> 16:23.750
If I let you come with us,
how do I know I can trust you?

16:26.500 --> 16:28.580
The Clave reinstated
the kill order on Jonathan.

16:29.580 --> 16:30.790
That means you too.

16:31.830 --> 16:33.830
I can't live without
you, Clary. I won't.

16:34.330 --> 16:36.920
And so if that means I have to
give up everything on everything

16:36.920 --> 16:40.460
I love to keep you safe...

16:40.460 --> 16:41.830
to keep you both safe...

16:45.500 --> 16:46.750
...then so be it.

16:46.750 --> 16:47.920
How touching,

16:47.920 --> 16:49.750
you're willing to put up
with me as the third wheel.

16:50.920 --> 16:53.420
I would never allow him
to treat you that way.

16:56.790 --> 16:58.580
How do I know this
isn't a trick?

17:00.670 --> 17:02.460
In your heart...

17:02.460 --> 17:04.750
you either know that
I'm telling the truth,

17:04.750 --> 17:06.620
or you don't.

17:06.620 --> 17:08.880
If you don't,
then leave me here.

17:10.750 --> 17:12.880
Excellent advice.
Let's go, sister.

17:12.880 --> 17:14.670
You're a Morgenstern;
you know better than this.

17:14.670 --> 17:16.880
I also know how
to make my own decisions.

17:19.790 --> 17:20.880
He's coming with us.

17:31.620 --> 17:33.790
(SOFT ELECTRONIC MUSIC)

17:38.880 --> 17:40.790
♪ Through your prism of love

17:43.710 --> 17:45.960
♪ I see the world in colour

17:45.960 --> 17:47.750
Can I have some
sprinkles, please?

17:48.830 --> 17:51.540
Oh, they don't have
those here, Madzie.

17:52.960 --> 17:56.710
I thought we were
teaching her restraint.

17:56.710 --> 17:57.830
I know, I know, but...

17:58.960 --> 18:00.670
...that face.

18:00.670 --> 18:03.750
♪ That love will keep me strong

18:06.710 --> 18:07.920
All right, sweet pea.

18:09.620 --> 18:10.920
♪ And I lost my mind

18:10.920 --> 18:13.750
♪ And I made you cry 1000 times

18:13.750 --> 18:16.540
♪ I guess I got
a little bit scared

18:16.540 --> 18:17.920
♪ I'm not prepared for you

18:17.920 --> 18:20.670
You know, you're gonna
be a hell of a dad.

18:22.580 --> 18:24.580
What? You don't think so?

18:26.620 --> 18:28.790
Well, to be honest,
I've never even considered it.

18:28.790 --> 18:31.620
Why not?
My father's a Prince of Hell.

18:31.620 --> 18:32.960
He's not exactly
a good role model.

18:32.960 --> 18:34.710
Well, my dad's
not perfect either.

18:34.710 --> 18:36.710
And look at us!

18:36.710 --> 18:38.580
We both turned out pretty OK.

18:40.960 --> 18:42.960
So, one can be a horrible parent

18:42.960 --> 18:44.920
without messing up their kids?

18:44.920 --> 18:46.750
Anything's possible...

18:49.000 --> 18:50.750
♪ Through your prism of love

18:53.540 --> 18:56.000
Besides, when it comes
to having a family...

18:57.000 --> 18:58.880
...you wouldn't be
doing it alone.

19:02.620 --> 19:03.790
♪ Prism of love ♪

19:07.040 --> 19:10.000
(CHURCH BELLS RINGING)

19:16.880 --> 19:18.000
Cover what runes you can.

19:18.000 --> 19:20.040
Where we're going, Shadowhunters
aren't appreciated.

19:20.040 --> 19:22.040
Right...

19:22.040 --> 19:23.830
And where exactly is that?

19:23.830 --> 19:25.710
Clearly, we're in Prague.

19:25.710 --> 19:27.750
A soldier's more effective

19:27.750 --> 19:29.000
with details.

19:29.000 --> 19:30.040
Did Daddy not teach you that?

19:31.920 --> 19:35.040
You'll be filled in
on a need-to-know basis.

19:35.040 --> 19:36.080
And while we're at it,

19:36.080 --> 19:38.750
I know you're here
to get rid of me, brother.

19:38.750 --> 19:41.040
And the second you slip,
I'll prove it.

19:41.040 --> 19:44.080
And then, it'll be
just me and Clary.

19:44.080 --> 19:46.000
The way it's meant to be.

19:47.000 --> 19:49.120
Are my two favourite boys
playing nice?

19:49.120 --> 19:50.880
So far.

19:54.960 --> 19:56.670
I dressed to kill.

19:57.920 --> 19:59.790
Only if the need arises.

20:00.790 --> 20:01.460
Shall we?

20:03.670 --> 20:04.880
Clary...

20:04.880 --> 20:06.790
Maybe you'd like to
tell me what the plan is

20:06.790 --> 20:07.830
for obtaining Morning Star.

20:07.830 --> 20:09.670
Jonathan didn't tell you?

20:09.670 --> 20:12.830
We are going to kidnap
the Seelie Queen.

20:12.830 --> 20:14.920
(RISING MUSIC)

20:18.790 --> 20:20.790
For the first time in 80 years,

20:20.790 --> 20:22.920
I was able to attend
morning mass.

20:22.920 --> 20:26.080
I sat in the sun and planted
flowers at my sister's grave...

20:26.080 --> 20:29.750
Oh, and you know that bakery
that invented cronuts?

20:29.750 --> 20:31.960
I stood in line today.

20:31.960 --> 20:33.710
Amazing.

20:33.710 --> 20:35.000
This is incredible.

20:35.420 --> 20:38.920
Sure. If you ignore the fact
that Aldertree tried

20:38.920 --> 20:40.920
to neutralize all of us
without our consent.

20:40.920 --> 20:42.880
I agree that was unconscionable.

20:42.880 --> 20:44.710
But Aldertree's been stopped.

20:44.710 --> 20:46.080
Think about what this means.

20:46.080 --> 20:48.040
The life you used to have,
all those times

20:48.040 --> 20:49.040
you wished you
could have it back.

20:50.710 --> 20:52.080
For the first time ever,
it's actually possible.

20:56.000 --> 20:58.830
Yeah, I'm... I'm not
so sure about that.

20:58.830 --> 21:00.040
What are you talking about?

21:00.040 --> 21:01.750
If the serum worked on you,

21:01.750 --> 21:03.000
why wouldn't it work on us?

21:04.960 --> 21:07.710
To stop Aldertree, we had
to destroy all the serum.

21:08.790 --> 21:10.960
It's gone...
except for a few vials.

21:12.750 --> 21:13.960
Well, where are those vials?

21:21.210 --> 21:24.960
As, um, someone who stuck
his fangs in your arm,

21:24.960 --> 21:26.830
I know it's a bit
hypocritical to ask,

21:26.830 --> 21:29.750
but, um... how big...

21:30.750 --> 21:32.170
That's big.

21:32.170 --> 21:34.040
Just don't think
about the needle.

21:34.040 --> 21:37.880
Imagine... you're Superman.

21:37.880 --> 21:40.120
And Clary is Lois Lane.

21:40.120 --> 21:43.880
And you're gonna reverse
the Earth's rotation

21:43.880 --> 21:45.790
to turn back time and save her.

21:45.790 --> 21:47.750
You watched Superman?!

21:47.750 --> 21:49.920
When did this world-shattering
event happen?

21:49.920 --> 21:51.000
Well, you always go on

21:51.000 --> 21:53.170
about how great
these superhero movies are.

21:53.170 --> 21:55.250
So, I wanted to see
what the fuss was about.

21:55.250 --> 21:56.960
And? What'd you think?

21:56.960 --> 21:59.000
Just because Clark Kent
had glasses,

21:59.000 --> 22:00.920
she couldn't tell
he was the same guy?

22:01.920 --> 22:04.000
If I was Lois, I would
have totally known.

22:04.000 --> 22:05.250
See, that's the fun
in it, though.

22:05.250 --> 22:08.040
The hot girl doesn't see
the geeky guy with glasses,

22:08.040 --> 22:10.920
until the hot girl realizes
that the geeky guy

22:10.920 --> 22:14.790
is totally awesome if she just
saw him for who he really is.

22:20.080 --> 22:23.120
I guess Lois just
needed some time

22:23.120 --> 22:24.880
to see what was
right in front of her.

22:26.080 --> 22:27.120
What?! Are we done?

22:27.120 --> 22:28.880
We are.

22:34.120 --> 22:36.170
CLARY: I've always heard
how beautiful Prague is.

22:36.170 --> 22:37.960
It's like a storybook.

22:37.960 --> 22:38.960
We'll have to come back.

22:38.960 --> 22:40.170
I'll take you for a boat
ride on the river.

22:40.170 --> 22:41.880
Sounds like a plan.

22:41.880 --> 22:42.880
Ahem...

22:44.000 --> 22:45.120
We're here.

22:47.210 --> 22:49.880
Clearly the bouncer
isn't happy about it.

22:49.880 --> 22:51.290
What's Kosti Lustr?

22:51.290 --> 22:53.290
It means Bone Chandelier.

22:53.290 --> 22:56.960
The Queen's favourite hangout,
for Downworlders only.

22:58.080 --> 23:00.210
Wait here. I'll work
my connections

23:00.210 --> 23:01.210
to get us inside.

23:03.250 --> 23:05.210
I'm watching you.

23:08.250 --> 23:11.120
Just... give him time.

23:11.120 --> 23:13.210
Once he trusts you,
he's like a puppy.

23:13.210 --> 23:15.080
All he wants is love.

23:17.290 --> 23:20.290
And all I want is you.

23:23.170 --> 23:25.170
Clary, do you remember
the first time we kissed?

23:26.170 --> 23:28.250
How could I forget?

23:31.000 --> 23:32.170
Please, come back to me.

23:32.170 --> 23:35.210
What are you talking about?
I'm... I'm right here.

23:37.080 --> 23:38.920
I love you so much.

23:45.170 --> 23:47.080
I love you too.

23:53.290 --> 23:56.000
I have to go help my brother
sweet talk us inside.

24:02.210 --> 24:03.330
ALEC: [Jace, you there?]

24:03.330 --> 24:05.040
[Yeah.]
ALEC: [Isabelle is working]

24:05.040 --> 24:07.250
[as fast as she can
to get Glorious re-forged.]

24:07.250 --> 24:08.290
[Where are you in Prague?]

24:08.290 --> 24:10.210
JACE: [Some club called
the Bone Chandelier.]

24:11.250 --> 24:13.210
The Bone Chandelier?

24:13.710 --> 24:16.290
Right before the Uprising,
I led a raid there to bring in

24:16.290 --> 24:18.670
some Seelie mercenaries.
Security's tight.

24:18.670 --> 24:20.250
But if we need to find
a way in, I can find it.

24:22.040 --> 24:23.170
Jace, how's Clary?

24:23.170 --> 24:26.250
[So far so good. But things
could get messy here.]

24:26.250 --> 24:28.170
[The plan is to kidnap
the Seelie Queen]

24:28.170 --> 24:30.210
[as a bargaining chip
to acquire Morning Star.]

24:30.210 --> 24:32.170
Are you kidding me?

24:32.170 --> 24:33.330
Is Jonathan trying
to get you all killed?

24:33.330 --> 24:35.120
[Yeah, well, me for sure.]

24:35.120 --> 24:37.330
[Apparently, the Queen comes
to this club once a month]

24:37.330 --> 24:39.330
[to party with her
fellow Downworlders.]

24:39.330 --> 24:42.210
ALEC: [If we warn her,
it'll blow your cover.]

24:42.210 --> 24:44.080
[Our best tactic right now]

24:44.080 --> 24:46.080
[is to get Glorious ready
and then make our move.]

24:46.080 --> 24:47.250
JACE: [The sooner the better.]

24:47.250 --> 24:50.080
[I just spotted a Seelie
with a blue sigil mark.]

24:50.080 --> 24:51.330
One of the Queen's elite guard.

24:51.330 --> 24:53.170
[Just watch your step.]

24:53.170 --> 24:56.000
[They won't hesitate
to kill you, Jonathan or Clary.]

24:56.000 --> 24:57.170
JACE: [Yeah, I'll do my best.]

25:00.170 --> 25:03.040
(SENTIMENTAL MUSIC)

25:07.120 --> 25:09.040
(WOMAN HARMONIZING)

25:12.080 --> 25:14.250
♪ I wanted to love you

25:14.250 --> 25:15.250
You're beautiful.

25:15.250 --> 25:17.330
♪ I'm still here because of you

25:17.330 --> 25:20.120
MAGNUS: Who are you?

25:20.120 --> 25:22.000
Alec.

25:22.000 --> 25:23.380
You continue to surprise me.

25:25.000 --> 25:26.330
There's nothing to be
ashamed of, Alec.

25:26.330 --> 25:28.000
You hold the pain here.

25:28.000 --> 25:29.290
Whatever it is,
I'm here for you.

25:29.290 --> 25:32.170
♪ Should I stay? Should I go?

25:32.170 --> 25:35.420
♪ If I didn't, you know

25:35.420 --> 25:37.000
♪ I'm here

25:37.000 --> 25:38.120
I know something's wrong.

25:38.120 --> 25:40.330
♪ Signals ♪

25:42.250 --> 25:44.080
Magnus, I... I love you.

25:44.080 --> 25:45.290
MAGNUS: I love you too.

25:50.330 --> 25:52.460
Maybe we're too...
Different?

25:52.460 --> 25:55.330
♪♪♪

26:11.210 --> 26:14.040
(OMINOUS MUSIC)

26:15.420 --> 26:17.170
Brother Zachariah.

26:18.330 --> 26:21.080
You said you were
in desperate need of my help.

26:22.330 --> 26:23.330
I am.

26:23.330 --> 26:25.080
What is it, Magnus?

26:26.170 --> 26:28.330
I need you to erase
all my memories of Alec.

26:30.210 --> 26:32.080
(RISING MUSIC)

26:38.500 --> 26:41.380
Should I take your silence
to mean you won't help me?

26:43.380 --> 26:45.330
No, my dear friend.

26:45.330 --> 26:47.500
I will always be here for you.

26:50.420 --> 26:51.500
You're speaking...

26:52.500 --> 26:55.080
Some words are too important

26:55.080 --> 26:57.120
not to be spoken aloud.

26:58.420 --> 27:02.170
Magnus... you've lost
great loves before.

27:02.170 --> 27:03.330
As have I.

27:04.500 --> 27:07.170
And as painful as
those memories may be,

27:07.170 --> 27:08.540
they are a part of who we are.

27:08.540 --> 27:10.380
I know.

27:13.380 --> 27:15.040
But Alec is different.

27:16.210 --> 27:18.120
Losing him, it...

27:19.170 --> 27:21.040
It's breaking me.

27:22.170 --> 27:23.460
I owe you my life,

27:23.460 --> 27:25.540
and I would do anything
to help you.

27:25.540 --> 27:27.580
For that very reason,

27:27.580 --> 27:30.210
I must refuse your request.

27:31.210 --> 27:32.290
How is that helping?

27:32.290 --> 27:34.210
I can't do this on my own!

27:34.210 --> 27:35.380
You can.

27:35.380 --> 27:39.420
Pull the memories from your mind
and send them to oblivion.

27:39.420 --> 27:41.330
You have the magic.

27:41.330 --> 27:43.420
You simply don't have the heart.

27:43.420 --> 27:45.210
Because deep down,

27:45.210 --> 27:47.080
you know you'll regret it.

27:48.420 --> 27:50.380
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

27:52.250 --> 27:54.420
I don't know what else to do.

27:54.420 --> 27:55.500
Magnus!

27:57.210 --> 27:58.540
If erasing Alec from your life

27:58.540 --> 28:01.210
is truly what you want...

28:01.210 --> 28:03.500
you'll find the strength
to do it on your own.

28:09.290 --> 28:11.170
Simon, I need to talk to you.

28:11.170 --> 28:12.620
I know you said
no interruptions,

28:12.620 --> 28:14.460
but they insisted it was urgent.

28:14.460 --> 28:16.420
The serum that made
Raphael a mundane,

28:16.420 --> 28:18.500
he said there was some left
and... is it in there?

28:18.500 --> 28:20.620
Don't touch that!
The serum is not there.

28:20.620 --> 28:23.210
I'm making a special sword
to save Clary from Jonathan.

28:23.210 --> 28:25.460
I thought you already captured
Jonathan. He's got Clary?

28:25.460 --> 28:27.420
It's a bit of a long story,
but bottom line,

28:27.420 --> 28:29.290
if we don't get
to her soon, it...

28:30.620 --> 28:32.500
Look, I... I'll talk to you
about the serum later.

28:32.500 --> 28:34.540
I promise.
Wait, so there is some left?

28:34.540 --> 28:37.330
Yes. After the extraction
for the sword for Clary,

28:37.330 --> 28:38.460
there's only one vial.

28:38.460 --> 28:39.460
Just one?!

28:41.460 --> 28:43.580
Unfortunately. And as
you can imagine,

28:43.580 --> 28:45.290
deciding who gets it is
a political minefield.

28:45.290 --> 28:47.210
Are you saying no one's
going to be able to get it?

28:47.210 --> 28:48.580
She's saying it's complicated.

28:48.580 --> 28:51.620
I don't understand. Why did you
have to destroy all of it?

28:51.620 --> 28:54.250
Was that really the only option?
You've robbed every Downworlder

28:54.250 --> 28:55.500
of a second chance
at a mundane life!

28:55.500 --> 28:57.330
Look, We didn't have
a choice! OK?

28:57.330 --> 29:01.210
Believe me... I get
wanting to go back.

29:01.210 --> 29:03.580
I almost killed my sister
and I had to make my mom

29:03.580 --> 29:05.250
believe that I was dead!

29:09.420 --> 29:12.210
We all had lives that
have been destroyed.

29:12.210 --> 29:14.170
I'm just trying to save Clary's.

29:21.580 --> 29:24.290
(ELECTRONIC MUSIC PLAYING)

29:24.290 --> 29:26.210
(OVERLAPPING SPEAKING)

29:42.670 --> 29:44.460
Nice chandelier.

29:45.620 --> 29:47.460
CLARY: Whose bones are those?

29:47.460 --> 29:49.710
Shadowhunters...

29:49.710 --> 29:52.540
Stick with me, sis. You won't
become part of the decor.

29:52.540 --> 29:54.290
Unless that Seelie sees you.

29:55.460 --> 29:56.620
The blue sigil mark
means he's part

29:56.620 --> 29:58.500
of the Queen's security detail.

29:58.500 --> 30:00.250
Probably best we don't
buy him a drink.

30:00.250 --> 30:03.500
See? I told you
he'd be an asset.

30:05.500 --> 30:08.500
♪♪♪

30:08.500 --> 30:11.580
Evening, Tsunae.
The regular, three shots.

30:13.330 --> 30:15.750
All right. The Queen
will arrive shortly.

30:15.750 --> 30:17.750
She'll be seated
at her favourite table.

30:17.750 --> 30:21.420
Our opportunity arises when her
head knight takes her upstairs

30:21.420 --> 30:23.330
for a rendez-vous with
her new warlock lover.

30:23.330 --> 30:24.750
That's when she'll
be vulnerable.

30:24.750 --> 30:26.580
Jace and I will
take out the knight.

30:26.580 --> 30:29.460
I grab the Queen, Clary portals
the three of us away.

30:29.460 --> 30:31.750
The four of us.
Including the Queen.

30:31.750 --> 30:34.580
Yeah, of course.
That's what I meant.

30:37.710 --> 30:40.250
(RISING MUSIC)

30:50.670 --> 30:52.710
What's going on?
What is this stuff?

30:52.710 --> 30:55.580
It's clearly some kind
of Seelie drug. Don't take it.

30:55.580 --> 30:58.420
Ah, surely you're not
against having a little fun?

30:59.460 --> 31:00.670
No!

31:02.790 --> 31:05.330
What's wrong? You know, all work

31:05.330 --> 31:06.710
and no play makes
Jace a dull boy.

31:06.710 --> 31:09.580
We are on mission.
We need to stay focused.

31:09.580 --> 31:11.540
Are you worried about everyone?
Or just you?

31:14.380 --> 31:15.380
Prove it.

31:21.620 --> 31:22.620
(GRUNTING)

31:31.500 --> 31:32.580
Happy now?

31:32.580 --> 31:34.330
Ecstatic.

31:40.790 --> 31:43.620
(ELECTRONIC MUSIC PLAYING)

31:43.620 --> 31:45.580
(CHEERING)

31:48.420 --> 31:50.380
[Alec, I need help.]

31:50.380 --> 31:53.460
Jace, talk to me.
[I don't have my stele and I...]

31:53.460 --> 31:55.670
[I can't focus enough
to activate my Iratze.]

31:55.670 --> 31:56.830
Are you hurt?

31:56.830 --> 31:59.380
[I...]
ALEC: [Jace, what's going on?]

31:59.380 --> 32:01.380
[I need you to focus.]
JACE: [I must've ingested]

32:01.380 --> 32:04.750
[a Seelie hallucinogen.
It's a silver liquid, bitter.]

32:04.750 --> 32:06.460
Are you able to stay alert?

32:06.460 --> 32:07.750
[I'm trying...]

32:07.750 --> 32:11.380
Jace? Jace, can you hear me?

32:11.380 --> 32:12.380
[Alec...]

32:12.380 --> 32:13.620
Glorious isn't ready yet.

32:13.620 --> 32:15.380
We're gonna portal in
and try and capture

32:15.380 --> 32:17.380
[Jonathan and Clary.]
JACE: [No! No!]

32:17.380 --> 32:19.420
[If we make a move
before we have Glorious,]

32:19.420 --> 32:20.620
[we'll lose Clary for good.]

32:20.620 --> 32:23.500
[I can hang in on my end.
Just get here with that sword!]

32:28.620 --> 32:29.750
You think you're gonna
get away with this?

32:31.500 --> 32:33.790
Dance floor. Now.

32:35.460 --> 32:36.670
♪ And stay awhile

32:37.830 --> 32:40.500
♪ I wish that I
could step inside

32:40.500 --> 32:44.380
♪ Your heart... and stay awhile

32:45.420 --> 32:47.790
♪ I wish that I
could step inside

32:47.790 --> 32:49.620
♪ Your heart

32:49.620 --> 32:50.790
Wait...

32:52.460 --> 32:54.380
What are you doing?

32:54.380 --> 32:55.790
You can tell me to stop
whenever you want...

32:57.540 --> 32:58.750
...but you won't.

32:59.790 --> 33:01.670
♪ Step inside

33:01.670 --> 33:03.500
♪ I could step inside

33:03.500 --> 33:05.500
